AS PASSED SENATE
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to state government,
2 so as to provide for the preservation of religious freedom; to provide for the granting of
3 relief; to provide for definitions; to provide for construction; to provide for statutory
4 interpretation; to provide for a short title; to provide for legislative findings and
5 determinations; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
6 purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Georgia Religious Freedom Restoration
10 Act."
11 SECTION 2.
12 The General Assembly finds and determines that:
13 (1) Whereas the framers of the United States Constitution and the people of this state,
14 recognizing free exercise of religion as an inalienable right, secured its protection in the
