37 (c) A person whose religious exercise has been burdened in violation of this chapter may
38 assert the violation as a claim or defense in a judicial proceeding and obtain appropriate
39 relief against government.
40 50-15A-2.
41 As used in this chapter, the term:
42 (1) 'Demonstrates' means meets the burden of going forward with the evidence and of
43 persuasion.
44 (2) 'Exercise of religion' means any exercise of religion, whether or not compelled by,
45 or central to, a system of religious belief, including, but not limited to, the practice or
46 observance of religion under Paragraphs III and IV of Section I, Article I of the
47 Constitution of this state or the Free Exercise Clause of the First Amendment to the
48 Constitution of the United States.
49 (3) 'Government' includes any branch, department, agency, instrumentality, and official
50 or other person acting under color of law of this state, or any political subdivision of this
51 state as defined in Code Section 50-15-1.
52 50-15A-3.
53 In any action or proceeding to enforce a provision of this chapter, the court or tribunal may
54 allow the prevailing party, other than government, a reasonable attorney fee as part of
55 costs; provided, however, that, in any action brought against a judicial officer for an act or
56 omission taken in such officer's judicial capacity, such officer shall not be held liable for
57 any costs, including attorney's fees, unless such action was clearly in excess of such
58 officer's jurisdiction.
